{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nDiscovered while implementing epic sonic-columned-sturgeon (op-certs). Children 4214 (merge-gate\nverify), ee0b (trusted-server producer), and 8f1d (HMACŌåÆopcert migration) all depend on a shared\nprimitive: **how an asymmetric op-cert (a DSSE envelope) is stored on a ticket and produced.** The\nepic decomposition treated this as implicit; it is a core event-sourcing change, so it gets its\nown ticket.\n\nToday attestations are HMAC records. `reducer/_processors.py::process_signature` builds the\n`attestations[kind]` record from a FIXED field set (manifest/algorithm/signature/key_id/head_sha/\nsigned_at/author/kind) ŌĆö it does NOT preserve an added `envelope`. Storing an op-cert DSSE envelope\ntherefore requires a reducer change (runs on every ticket replay; the SNAPSHOT/compaction fold at\n`_processors.py:763` restores `attestations` verbatim, so op-cert fields survive compaction for\nfree) plus a producer in `signing.py`.\n\n## Selected design ŌĆö Option A (DECIDED 2026-07-13 by Joe Oakhart; no further confirmation needed)\nExtend the existing `SIGNATURE` event record ŌĆö do NOT introduce a new event type. This mirrors git\nsigned commits (a `gpgsig` header added to the existing commit object, tolerant-reader:\nold clients ignore the unknown field) and additive Protobuf/Avro schema evolution. Concretely:\n\n- **Producer** (`signing.sign_opcert_manifest`, parallel to `sign_manifest`): builds a DSSE\n  envelope via `opcert.sign_opcert(ticket_id, material_fingerprint, merged_log_commit,\n  key_path=ŌĆ”, principal=ŌĆ”)`, then appends a `SIGNATURE` event whose record carries the signed\n  `manifest` (first line `\"<kind>: ŌĆ”\"` so the reducer derives the kind), the encoded `envelope`\n  (`dsse.encode`), the bound `material_fingerprint` + `merged_log_commit`, and `algorithm=\"sshsig\"`\n  ŌĆö NO HMAC signature.\n- **Reducer** (`process_signature`): additionally preserve `envelope`, `material_fingerprint`,\n  `merged_log_commit` into the `attestations[kind]` record (read via `data.get(...)`, present-only).\n  No change needed to the compaction fold (it restores `attestations` verbatim).\n- **Read helper** (`opcert.opcert_from_record`): returns `(dsse.Envelope, {material_fingerprint,\n  merged_log_commit})` when the record carries an `envelope`, else `None` (distinguishes an op-cert\n  record from a legacy HMAC record).\n- **Rollout:** the new fields are additive and preserved-and-ignored by older clones (upgrade\n  reconcile hosts first), mirroring the `TAG_DELTA` precedent.\n\n(Considered and rejected: Option B ŌĆö a new `OPCERT` event type + separate `opcerts` map ŌĆö cleaner\nseparation but larger change and its separation is moot once 8f1d removes HMAC.)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `signing.sign_opcert_manifest(...)` writes an envelope-bearing `SIGNATURE` event; a test\n      asserts the ticket's reduced `attestations[<kind>]` record then carries the encoded\n      `envelope` + bound `material_fingerprint`/`merged_log_commit`, and NO HMAC `signature`.\n- [ ] `process_signature` preserves those fields through a full reduce AND through a\n      compact-then-replay round-trip; a test asserts an op-cert survives compaction unchanged.\n- [ ] `opcert.opcert_from_record(record)` returns `(envelope, bound_fields)` for an op-cert record\n      and `None` for a legacy HMAC record (test both); the returned envelope, fed to\n      `opcert.verify_opcert` with a pinned keyring, certifies (end-to-end test).\n- [ ] The new record fields are additive (present-only): a test asserts a legacy HMAC\n      `sign_manifest` record is byte-unchanged (no `envelope`/bound keys), so older clones\n      preserve-and-ignore. Rollout note documented (upgrade reconcile hosts first).\n\n## Success Criteria\n- 4214 can read a stored op-cert to verify it over the merged log; ee0b/8f1d can produce op-certs\n  onto tickets via `sign_opcert_manifest`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783984083487938001,"uuid":"6eef2846-92f9-499a-b84f-408d8c312c9d"}